column3: response
I recently read, The Chronicles of Narnia, to my younger sister. The book made me think about wrong and right, and nature, too.
My dad and I just got into the Harry Potter books. We're kind of late to the party!
We watched, Charlotte's Web, that is a book. It's a made-up story about friendships.
I've been reading A Wrinkle in Time. I thought they did a pretty good job with the movie.
I like the magic in The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe, by C.S. Lewis.
I think the Diary of a Wimpy Kid is so funny.
I like to read National Geographic Kids. They have some great articles about how we can take care of our planet and what animals are endangered because people are destroying their habitats.
I like adventures to different times and places, like the Magic Tree House series.
I love stories of real people and things that happened.
I read the cafeteria menu everyday. I'm always waiting for them to bring the chicken sandwich back.
I like to read signs on the street. It lets me know what's happening. I read about a lost dog this morning that I am going to watch out for.
I like to read manuals and then match them up to the youtube video, if I can.

I like the Percy Jackson books, but not the graphic novels. You can't really use your imagination when they give you all the pictures, especially when it's not like how I imagined it when I was reading the books.
I've been enjoying the The Chronicles of Narnia series. Who wouldn't like to live in a world full of talking animals?
I like the Series of Unfortunate Events books because of the mystery.
